How to use Mobikul toast library.

1) Enable the databinding flag in your module level gradle file.
2) Copy the customtoastrelease.aar file in your system.( smb://192.168.15.107/public/Anchit/customtoastrelease.aar)
3) IMPORT this file from your system to your android studio project
4) Check your module level gradle file contains this line ( "compile project(':customtoastrelease')" )

For checking the demo of how the dialogs will appear. Install the apk in your device (smb://192.168.15.107/public/Anchit/mobikul_toast_library_demo.apk).

For raising any issue or point that you feel should be includedin the library, comment or raise an issue over here https://webkulgit.com/anchit.makkar849/CustomToast/issues


Sample Code Usage :

1)                 CustomToast.getInstantToast(this, CustomToast.InstantToastType.SUCCESS).show();

2)                 CustomToast customToast = new CustomToast(this);
                   customToast.setToastPosition(CustomToast.ToastPosition.TOP);
                   customToast.setToastIcon(getResources().getDrawable(android.R.drawable.btn_star));
                   customToast.setToastIcon(ContextCompat.getDrawable(this, android.R.drawable.btn_star));
                   customToast.setIconPosition(CustomToast.IconPosition.END);
                   customToast.setToastText(R.string.my_dummy_text);
                   customToast.setTextSize(12, TypedValue.COMPLEX_UNIT_DIP);
                   customToast.setToastBackground(CustomToast.ToastBackgroundType.OVAL);
                   customToast.setToastBackgroundColor(Color.BLUE);
                   customToast.setToastTextColor(ContextCompat.getColor(this, R.color.colorPrimary));
                   customToast.show();